1
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:41,833
<i>No, I'm not going to answer
the phone.</i>

2
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:44,733
<i>I know that you want
to answer it.</i>

3
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:45,900
<i> No-</i>

4
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:49,600
<i>Hello, this is Noah Salvador,
Felma's fiancé.</i>

5
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:51,433
<i>Jessica, is your father
beside you?</i>

6
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:54,733
<i>Manuel, please stop
bothering us.</i>

7
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:55,733
<i> We're getting married soon.</i>

8
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:57,733
<i>I'm sorry about what happened
to you.</i>

9
00:00:57,867 --> 00:01:02,267
<i>But please, stop involving Felma
and the kids in your problem.</i>

10
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,567
<i>You didn't eat
your breakfast again?</i>

11
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,667
<i> What's the matter with you?</i>

12
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:09,333
<i>Just let me know if you
don't want to eat.</i>

13
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,800
<i>You're wasting food and my time!</i>

14
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,167
<i> Why did you do that?</i>

15
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:18,967
<i>As your fiancé, I think I have
the right to put a stop</i>

16
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:20,267
<i> to whatever Manuel is doing.</i>

17
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,700
<i>But he's not doing
anything wrong.</i>

18
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:24,467
<i>You care more about his feelings
than mine.</i>

19
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:25,633
<i>It's starting to hurt
my feelings, Felma.</i>

20
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:27,467
<i>I think we need to give
each other some space.</i>

21
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,433
<i> Are you breaking up with me?</i>

22
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,733
<i>Are you cancelling our wedding?</i>

23
00:01:30,867 --> 00:01:32,467
<i>Is that what you want to happen?</i>

24
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:35,933
<i>Uncle Noah caught mom talking
to the man from Canada.</i>

25
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:37,267
<i> I just asked how he's doing</i>

26
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:39,933
<i>because your dad is not going
to be able to walk again.</i>

27
00:01:53,067 --> 00:01:56,733
Miss, don't forget to
clean his navel, please.

28
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,533
Clean that properly.

29
00:01:58,667 --> 00:01:59,600
Yes, Ma'am.

30
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:00,733
I'll do that later.

31
00:02:00,867 --> 00:02:02,300
I'm not done yet.

32
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:06,367
Clean under his arms too,
to make sure he won't smell.

33
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:08,700
You know what I mean, bad odor.

34
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,667
Don't worry, I'll do that.

35
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,100
Let me finish my job.

36
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:13,900
I know the drill, Ma'am.

37
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:17,600
Oh my, if I don't tell you what
to do, you won't do it right.

38
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:21,000
And can you put a little force
on it?

39
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:21,967
You need to put a little
more force

40
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,600
because he has a lot of grime.

41
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:26,767
It's been a while since
he got a decent bath.

42
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:28,600
Oh my, you're taking too long.

43
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:29,867
You're so slow.

44
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:34,233
Didn't I tell you to rub harder?

45
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:38,633
Ma'am, he's an elderly person.

46
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:40,900
We need to be gentle with him.

47
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,767
You're just lazy!

48
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,867
I've been watching you!

49
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
And you move too slowly!

50
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:50,833
You're like a low-battery cell
phone.

51
00:02:50,967 --> 00:02:52,133
No energy!

52
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:53,600
If I had done it myself,

53
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:55,067
it could have been done
a while ago!

54
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,500
Why don't you do it then?

55
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:57,933
Since you know better than I do.

56
00:02:58,067 --> 00:03:00,167
You're starting to piss me off.

57
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,833
You meddle too much.

58
00:03:01,967 --> 00:03:03,667
You're bold, aren't you?

59
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:07,533
Let me remind you,
you're the nurse here!

60
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:10,200
So do your job right!

61
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,033
Hey, what's going on?

62
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,800
Stop fighting!

63
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:15,300
I'm doing my job right.

64
00:03:15,433 --> 00:03:17,133
You're just a know-it-all!

65
00:03:17,267 --> 00:03:19,700
If you know how to do it,
then do it yourself!

66
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:20,733
You're rude!

67
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:21,800
Wait!

68
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:22,900
And you have the guts
to talk back to me!

69
00:03:23,033 --> 00:03:24,967
Did you think I'll let
you get away with this?

70
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:26,300
I will report you
to this hospital!

71
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:27,500
And you will lose your job!

72
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:28,500
Go ahead!

73
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:29,933
You think you're a hotshot!

74
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,500
So you married a Canadian,

75
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,500
and you think you're better
than everyone else!

76
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:33,133
You're rude!

77
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:35,067
I said, stop fighting!

78
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,233
You just want his money!

79
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:40,500
You can't wait for him to die,
right?

80
00:03:40,633 --> 00:03:42,133
You're rude!

81
00:03:42,267 --> 00:03:43,167
You're not just rude.

82
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:47,033
Here!

83
00:03:50,467 --> 00:03:52,233
Let me go!

84
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:54,867
I said let me go!

85
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:56,033
Sir? Sir!

86
00:03:56,167 --> 00:03:57,833
Sir! Let me help you.

87
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:59,367
I'm sorry, Sir.

88
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,100
Sir.

89
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:03,433
Sorry, Sir. Okay.

90
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:08,167
Are you okay?

91
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,600
I think so.

92
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:22,467
I agree with Andrea.

93
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,500
It's Karma.

94
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:26,033
That's what he deserves.

95
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:27,267
Jeffrey.

96
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,833
You shouldn't think like
that, it's not right.

97
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,067
And he's your dad!

98
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,467
Mom, I don't think of him
as my dad.

99
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,867
Why are we on this again?

100
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,100
Don't you feel bad for him?

101
00:04:37,233 --> 00:04:38,133
Why?

102
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:41,133
Did he feel bad for us
when he abandoned us?

103
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:42,667
Yeah, you were a baby,

104
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,700
so you didn't feel the pain we
felt.

105
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:49,633
Jeff, it's not easy
to be a cripple.

106
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:52,100
Mom, we were also crippled
when he left us.

107
00:04:52,233 --> 00:04:55,267
If you lost a husband, we also
lost a father.

108
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,800
We went through hardship to be
on our toes again.

109
00:04:57,933 --> 00:04:59,067
We crawl through poverty.

110
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,167
Now it's his turn to crawl,
literally.

111
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:02,733
Jeff, stop!

112
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:05,233
Why are you defending him?

113
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:07,500
Worst of all, you're letting
your relationship

114
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:09,933
with Uncle Noah fall apart
because of him!

115
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:12,233
Mom, you already found an angel.

116
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:14,733
Why do you care more
about that devil?

117
00:05:14,867 --> 00:05:16,267
Are you still in
your right mind?

118
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,567
Don't ever talk to me like that!

119
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:21,467
Just because I listened
to your opinion

120
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,900
doesn't give you the right
to disrespect me.

121
00:05:24,033 --> 00:05:25,633
I'm still your mom!

122
00:05:25,767 --> 00:05:27,667
I'm sorry, Mom.

123
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:31,300
You know how I get
when it comes to him.

124
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,900
Mom, we just don't want
your relationship

125
00:05:36,067 --> 00:05:38,733
with Uncle Noah to fall apart.

126
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:41,900
Your wedding is in jeopardy
because of him.

127
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:45,933
Mom, Uncle Noah's been with us
for a long time now.

128
00:05:46,067 --> 00:05:50,067
Don't throw that away
for someone who abandoned us.

129
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:53,733
Be honest, Mom, have you
done anything to fix things

130
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:55,333
between you and Uncle Noah?

131
00:05:55,467 --> 00:05:58,000
Did you even try to talk to him?

132
00:05:58,133 --> 00:06:00,133
I'm sorry to say this,

133
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:03,333
but you're letting your pride
ruin things.

134
00:06:03,467 --> 00:06:07,033
Seriously, are you willing
to let Uncle Noah go

135
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,133
for Coleen's dad?

136
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:09,133
He's our dad.

137
00:06:09,267 --> 00:06:11,200
You're the only one
who calls him "Dad".

138
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:17,333
Mom, I'm begging you.

139
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:20,600
Please, talk to Uncle Noah.

140
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:23,500
Because I will never
accept your ex-husband.

141
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,600
Me either.

142
00:06:27,733 --> 00:06:29,100
I won't accept him.

143
00:06:37,867 --> 00:06:38,667
What?

144
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,567
Mom, you got fired from work?

145
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:45,933
Go ahead, raise your voice
so your dad can hear you.

146
00:06:46,067 --> 00:06:48,533
Mom, can't they give you
a warning or something

147
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,267
instead of firing you?

148
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:57,067
It's better than getting sued.

149
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,833
Because the patient who tried
to intervene in the fight

150
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,600
fell off the bed.

151
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:06,533
Honestly, I'm lucky
because the HR begged them

152
00:07:06,667 --> 00:07:08,633
not to press charges.

153
00:07:08,767 --> 00:07:12,867
Besides, I've got a few
warnings already

154
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,100
because of my tardiness.

155
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:17,733
But what else can I do?

156
00:07:17,867 --> 00:07:20,800
I have to take care of your dad
before I go to work.

157
00:07:20,933 --> 00:07:23,300
It's too much.

158
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,000
What are we going to do now?

159
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,467
Talk about bad luck...

160
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:36,767
You know what, I think
everything fell apart

161
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:40,767
when we got back
from the Philippines.

162
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:44,567
Ever since your dad and
Felma's paths crossed.

163
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:46,600
I think that woman
put a curse on us.

164
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:50,200
We brought that curse
with us here in Canada.

165
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:53,233
Mom, please don't blame
Miss Felma

166
00:07:53,367 --> 00:07:56,500
for everything that's going
wrong.

167
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:58,200
What?

168
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,233
So, who do you
want me to blame?

169
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:01,333
It's your dad's fault,

170
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:02,767
because he met up
with that woman.

171
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:04,700
And wait a minute,

172
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:08,333
why are you calling her
Miss Felma?

173
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:11,400
It's Mistress Felma!

174
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:13,033
That's what she is.

175
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:21,000
Wait a minute,
tell me the truth.

176
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:24,667
Are you still communicating
with that woman?

177
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,067
No, I'm not.

178
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:32,067
You better not!

179
00:08:35,367 --> 00:08:37,767
What are we going to do now?

180
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,800
I need to find a job right away.

181
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:46,467
But it will be hard,
as long as I'm responsible

182
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,833
for caring for your dad.

183
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:51,700
What do you mean?

184
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:54,700
I have to let go of your dad.

185
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,867
I can't take care of him
anymore.

186
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
I need to send him
to a nursing home.

187
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:00,767
What? No way!

188
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:02,267
I'm not okay with that!

189
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:05,100
Well, I'm not asking you
for your permission!

190
00:09:05,233 --> 00:09:06,733
I'm just letting you know.

191
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:17,800
Mom, maybe there's another way
to deal with this.

192
00:09:22,633 --> 00:09:23,533
Sure.

193
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,500
What do you want?

194
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:27,733
You want me to stay at home,

195
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,833
take care of your dad
round the clock?

196
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:30,767
Okay.

197
00:09:32,767 --> 00:09:34,367
But what about our bills?

198
00:09:35,933 --> 00:09:37,500
What about your schooling?

199
00:09:37,633 --> 00:09:39,033
How are we going to pay
for all of that?

200
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:41,600
I can take a break for now.

201
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:43,600
I will take care of him.

202
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:44,533
Come on.

203
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,000
Can you knock it off?

204
00:09:47,067 --> 00:09:48,667
I'm a nurse, and I'm having a
hard time taking care of him.

205
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,700
I can only imagine how hard
it could be for you.

206
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:53,167
What do you know
about caring for a cripple?

207
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,400
Go to school.

208
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:56,033
For your future.

209
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:58,000
We need to be practical.

210
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:02,333
I'm going to talk to
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson tomorrow.

211
00:10:03,733 --> 00:10:05,067
So that...

212
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,667
they can help us with the
expenses for his nursing home.

213
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,667
Mom, does Dad know about this?

214
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,233
What if he won't agree?

215
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:16,533
Mom, I'm not sure if I can
bear being away from him.

216
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:18,333
Well, you have to bear it.

217
00:10:18,467 --> 00:10:19,533
We have no choice.

218
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:21,933
And your dad
doesn't have a say in this.

219
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:25,133
I will accept
any decision you make, Hazel.

220
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:27,133
Dad.

221
00:10:27,267 --> 00:10:30,100
Your life can't revolve
around taking care of me.

222
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:32,567
You also have your own life.

223
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,400
I don't want to be a burden.

224
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:37,067
I think it's better that...

225
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,000
I stay at the nursing home.

226
00:10:42,467 --> 00:10:43,733
Dad.

227
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:46,767
Dad, I don't want
that to happen.

228
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,067
I won't let it happen, Dad.

229
00:10:54,867 --> 00:10:59,600
Dad, I don't want
to be away from you.

230
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:13,267
The space is more
for her than for me.

231
00:11:15,367 --> 00:11:16,600
Everything is clear to me, son.

232
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:20,367
I know that I love your mom and
I want to marry her, son.

233
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,700
I just want to make sure
that she wants to do the same.

234
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,833
I want to know if she loves me

235
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,633
and wants to marry me.

236
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:33,000
Uncle, I'm begging you.

237
00:11:34,367 --> 00:11:36,667
Please, don't give up on my mom.

238
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,333
I will never give up on her.

239
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,833
But what if she wants
to give up on us?

240
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:47,567
How can I fight for someone
who wouldn't fight for me?

241
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:59,600
Sis, is it wrong to be concerned
about your ex-husband?

242
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:02,567
Does it always have...

243
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,200
to be taken the wrong way?

244
00:12:06,467 --> 00:12:08,933
Is pity all you feel for him?

245
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:12,600
To be fair, though,

246
00:12:12,733 --> 00:12:16,100
I do feel bad
about what happened to Manuel.

247
00:12:16,267 --> 00:12:18,467
But here's the thing,
Abel says...

248
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:23,833
he knows nothing about it. They
don't talk about what happened.

249
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:30,700
But to be honest,
I feel worse for Noah.

250
00:12:32,867 --> 00:12:36,600
Because he waited for so long

251
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:37,733
for you to reciprocate
his feelings.

252
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:40,000
He waited
for more than a decade.

253
00:12:40,133 --> 00:12:45,433
And after all that, when
you finally give him your love.

254
00:12:45,567 --> 00:12:47,400
What did you do?

255
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:53,933
You made him feel like you care
more about your ex-husband.

256
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,500
Sis!

257
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:59,267
Are you a sadist?
That's not good!

258
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,667
Admit it.

259
00:13:02,033 --> 00:13:06,900
Girl, you're living proof
that there's only a thin line

260
00:13:07,033 --> 00:13:10,700
between being a martyr
and a fool.

261
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:12,833
Sorry not sorry, Sis.

262
00:13:12,967 --> 00:13:15,400
I'm just being honest.

263
00:13:15,533 --> 00:13:17,033
Because the way you're acting
right now,

264
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:20,467
it clearly shows
that you're still in love

265
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,933
with your ex-husband!

266
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:26,667
Your ex-husband, who abandoned
you and your children!

267
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:27,700
Am I right?

268
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:33,300
I think your mom hasn't
really moved on from your dad.

269
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:36,333
My gosh, that's what
we don't understand.

270
00:13:38,767 --> 00:13:40,633
After he abandoned us
for so many years,

271
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:42,233
my mom still defends him.

272
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:44,667
To be fair to your mom,

273
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:48,233
I do feel...

274
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:49,567
and it's clear to me...

275
00:13:51,467 --> 00:13:52,300
that she loves me...

276
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,667
or used to love me.

277
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,800
But admit it or not,

278
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:00,967
it's clear that she loves your
dad more than she loves me.

279
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:04,300
I'll always be second
in her heart.

280
00:14:06,867 --> 00:14:08,300
It's not fair, Uncle.

281
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:14,433
You're more like a dad to us
than that man ever did.

282
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,567
What seems unfair to us

283
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,533
may not seem fair to her.

284
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:25,267
Perhaps that's the definition
of love. Blind.

285
00:14:26,433 --> 00:14:27,367
If that's the case,

286
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:30,433
how can I force myself on
someone who doesn't want me?

287
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,167
It's not up to me, Jeff.

288
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:38,433
Mr. Perfect is right
in front of you, sis.

289
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:42,967
So please, I'm begging
you, please...

290
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:48,667
As your bestie, you
have to talk to Noah.

291
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,967
Win him back, swallow your
pride.

292
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:57,733
Admit it or not, this time...

293
00:14:57,867 --> 00:15:00,300
you're in the wrong!

294
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:18,033
Dad,

295
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,600
I'll miss you so much.

296
00:15:20,733 --> 00:15:21,567
I love you.

297
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:24,133
I love you, sweetie.
Don't cry.

298
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:28,467
Whenever you're free, you will
visit me, okay?

299
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,067
I will, I promise.

300
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:34,700
So, let's go.

301
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:38,867
Mom, can I come with you
to the nursing home?

302
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,033
No.

303
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:44,200
Stay here.
You have a lot to do.

304
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:46,067
Do the laundry.

305
00:15:51,967 --> 00:15:53,033
Go on.

306
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:15,933
Mom.

307
00:16:16,067 --> 00:16:19,467
I want to know how dad is doing.

308
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:29,200
Sweetie, I know that you're
worried about your dad.

309
00:16:30,433 --> 00:16:31,233
But...

310
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,967
your brother and sister will be
mad if they find out.

311
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:39,333
You know how they are.

312
00:16:39,467 --> 00:16:40,800
Mom,

313
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,300
they won't find out.

314
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:45,200
We will keep it a secret.

315
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,467
I'm good at keeping secrets.

316
00:16:49,033 --> 00:16:50,100
Please?

317
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:03,300
Mr. and Mrs Wilson suggested
this nursing home.

318
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,567
Don't worry, you'll get used
to their routine.

319
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:12,800
Anyway, just read the schedule
guide they gave you earlier.

320
00:17:12,933 --> 00:17:17,633
And if you need assistance
to the restroom,

321
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,167
use the buzzer.

322
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,200
The staff will come to help you.

323
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:26,333
They're called
personal support workers.

324
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:32,100
And for food, you can eat
in the common dining room.

325
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:35,033
And if you want, you can
ask them to bring you food here.

326
00:17:35,167 --> 00:17:37,033
Okay, I got it.

327
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,900
Okay, I have to go.
I have a job interview.

328
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,033
Hazel,

329
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:49,100
thank you so much.

330
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,467
It's okay, you're welcome.

331
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,400
Jessica and I will come
to visit you.

332
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:00,833
Be safe.

333
00:18:09,467 --> 00:18:10,433
I'll go ahead.

334
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:14,333
Sir Manuel,

335
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:19,033
are you ready for the tour
of our facilities?

336
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:20,800
I would love to accompany you.

337
00:18:22,133 --> 00:18:23,100
Okay.

338
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:26,200
Please, follow me.
Or would you like me to assist?

339
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,100
Okay.

340
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,933
It just keeps on ringing,

341
00:19:05,067 --> 00:19:06,267
no one's picking up.

342
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:10,433
Mom,

343
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:15,267
what if they think someone
might try to pick a fight

344
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,533
with them again if they pick up
the phone?

345
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:20,300
At least,

346
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:22,300
we tried to call them.

347
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,233
I'm gonna get some rest.

348
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:27,767
Mom, wait.

349
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,900
- What is it?
- I have an idea. Come here.

350
00:19:30,067 --> 00:19:30,933
What idea?

351
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:34,467
Here.

352
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:37,267
Smile!

353
00:19:38,567 --> 00:19:39,567
There...

354
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:42,467
What are you going to do?

355
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:43,433
Sweetie.

356
00:19:43,567 --> 00:19:45,567
Wait.

357
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:47,300
I'm going to chat with them.

358
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:52,533
Hello, this is Coleen.

359
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,567
Don't worry.

360
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:58,833
It's just my mom and me.

361
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,133
Are you with Dad?

362
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,900
I'm alone, I'll call you.

363
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:19,767
She hasn't replied?

364
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:21,000
Wait, Mom.

365
00:20:21,133 --> 00:20:22,000
Mom!

366
00:20:22,133 --> 00:20:24,100
Be patient.

367
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,033
I'm so tired.

368
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:26,000
Mom, mom!

369
00:20:26,133 --> 00:20:27,367
Come sit down.

370
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,233
She replied.

371
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,033
What did they say?

372
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:32,333
She said she'll call us.

373
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,533
I am absolutely sure you
will like our facilities

374
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:42,000
and our gardens
and the golf course.

375
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:44,800
And our chefs are
particularly trained

376
00:20:44,933 --> 00:20:51,167
to make dishes that are special
for every dietary requirement

377
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:54,000
and for the preferences
of our residents.

378
00:20:54,133 --> 00:20:56,733
Is there anything in particular
you would love to have

379
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:57,700
for dinner tonight?

380
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:59,467
Thank you.

381
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:04,067
How about a Canadian specialty?
Lobster Thermidor?

382
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,633
Would you like to try that?

383
00:21:05,767 --> 00:21:08,700
That would be lovely.
It's also our house specialty.

384
00:21:08,867 --> 00:21:11,167
I am sure
you will absolutely love

385
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:13,700
being part
of the Royal House family.

386
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:38,600
Hi.

387
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:39,933
<i> Hello, Jessica.</i>

388
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:41,833
Hello there,
Miss Felma and Coleen.

389
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,167
Where's dad?

390
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:49,267
<i> Actually, that's the bad news.</i>

391
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,933
My mom brought him
to a nursing home.

392
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:54,567
Nursing home?

393
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:57,833
<i>Someone else will take care of
him over there?</i>

394
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,433
I didn't want him to go.

395
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:01,833
But it's my mom's decision,

396
00:22:01,967 --> 00:22:05,233
there's nothing I could do
to stop her.

397
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:07,967
That's sad to hear.

398
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:11,167
Jessica, I'm sorry about
what happened last time.

399
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:15,200
I didn't expect that...

400
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:19,300
<i>that Noah will answer your call.</i>

401
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:22,133
I think it's my fault.

402
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:25,733
My mom didn't want me
to call you anymore.

403
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:28,600
But I disobeyed her.

404
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:32,433
<i>Actually, at that time,
Dad was sitting beside me.</i>

405
00:22:32,567 --> 00:22:34,833
<i> I was calling on his behalf.</i>

406
00:22:34,967 --> 00:22:37,300
<i> He just wants to apologize</i>

407
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:39,633
<i>for all the pain
he has caused you.</i>

408
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:49,300
Jessica, can you please tell Dad
that I'm always thinking of him

409
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:52,133
<i> and praying for him?</i>

410
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:56,067
Of course.

411
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,767
<i>He'll be very happy to hear it
for sure.</i>

412
00:23:03,667 --> 00:23:07,233
Jessica, thank you.

413
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:08,367
Until our next...

414
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:13,000
<i> Jessica, wait!</i>

415
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:15,100
<i> I have a favor to ask.</i>

416
00:23:31,467 --> 00:23:33,967
One of the staff members
told me earlier

417
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,933
that you're not eating
your lunch.

418
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:39,933
And you don't interact
with the other residents.

419
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:42,400
They said, you just stayed
in your room.

420
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:48,167
Sweetie, I'm still adapting
to this place.

421
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:50,867
I haven't adjusted yet.

422
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,133
Wait dad.

423
00:23:53,267 --> 00:23:55,533
I have something to show you.

424
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,167
It's a surprise.

425
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:00,500
Dad.

426
00:24:00,633 --> 00:24:02,800
<i> Hi, Dad!</i>

427
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:06,233
<i> How are you doing?</i>

428
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,367
<i>I'm Coleen,
your youngest daughter.</i>

429
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,867
<i> Dad...</i>

430
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,167
<i> You know what?</i>

431
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:25,333
<i>I've been wanting to do
this for a long time now.</i>

432
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:31,267
<i>But whenever I say that
I want to talk to you.</i>

433
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:34,233
<i> Jeffrey and Andrea stop me.</i>

434
00:24:34,367 --> 00:24:36,633
<i> They always get mad at me.</i>

435
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:40,100
<i>Actually, Mom gets mad at me,
too, at first.</i>

436
00:24:40,233 --> 00:24:42,267
<i> But, she's okay now.</i>

437
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:48,667
<i>Dad, I've been wanting
to see you.</i>

438
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:52,333
<i>I really want to know you, Dad.</i>

439
00:24:52,467 --> 00:24:59,833
<i>I want to hold you,
to hug you...</i>

440
00:24:59,967 --> 00:25:03,400
<i> I want to call you "Dad".</i>

441
00:25:03,567 --> 00:25:06,700
<i> But I'm okay now.</i>

442
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:11,800
<i>Because now I can say that
I finally know who I am.</i>

443
00:25:15,767 --> 00:25:20,700
<i>I still hope that my dream
will come true.</i>

444
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:26,833
<i> So, Dad, please get well soon.</i>

445
00:25:26,967 --> 00:25:28,167
<i> Get your strength back.</i>

446
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:31,100
<i> And be safe.</i>

447
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:35,400
<i>So that I can meet you someday.</i>

448
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:43,400
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

449
00:25:43,533 --> 00:25:46,033
<i>I will wait for the day
that I meet you.</i>

450
00:25:53,733 --> 00:25:55,533
I love you so much, Coleen.

451
00:25:58,433 --> 00:26:00,567
Dad loves you so much.

452
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:17,133
What makes you think
that I'm not your ally?

453
00:26:17,267 --> 00:26:18,733
I'm team Noah!

454
00:26:18,867 --> 00:26:21,667
Now, we have to do something

455
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:24,400
so Uncle Noah and Mom can patch
things up.

456
00:26:24,533 --> 00:26:28,933
I prayed and I thought hard
about my decision.

457
00:26:29,067 --> 00:26:31,467
Let's not get married.

458
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,333
Let's watch Coleen's video,

459
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:36,433
and then I want to make a video
for her.

460
00:26:36,567 --> 00:26:38,167
- Can we do that?
- Here.
